# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Redrob Hackathon v4 — Submission Validation Dockerfile
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This Dockerfile creates a sandboxed environment that validates your
# submission CSV against ALL requirements from the submission spec.
#
# It does NOT inspect your ranking code contents. It only checks:
#   ✔ CSV format (header, row count, column types)
#   ✔ Rank uniqueness and completeness (1-100)
#   ✔ Score monotonicity (non-increasing)
#   ✔ candidate_id format and existence in candidates.jsonl
#   ✔ Reasoning quality warnings
#   ✔ Repository structure (README, requirements, metadata)
#   ✔ Environment constraints (memory limit, network block)
#
# USAGE:
#   1. Build:
#      docker build -t redrob-validator -f Dockerfile.validate .
#
#   2. Validate CSV only (quick check):
#      docker run --rm \
#        -v "$(pwd):/workspace" \
#        redrob-validator \
#        --csv /workspace/submission.csv
#
#   3. Validate CSV + check candidate_ids exist in dataset:
#      docker run --rm \
#        -v "$(pwd):/workspace" \
#        -v "/path/to/candidates.jsonl:/workspace/candidates.jsonl:ro" \
#        redrob-validator \
#        --csv /workspace/submission.csv \
#        --candidates /workspace/candidates.jsonl
#
#   4. Full validation (CSV + candidates + repo structure):
#      docker run --rm \
#        -v "$(pwd):/workspace" \
#        -v "/path/to/candidates.jsonl:/workspace/candidates.jsonl:ro" \
#        redrob-validator \
#        --csv /workspace/submission.csv \
#        --candidates /workspace/candidates.jsonl \
#        --repo-root /workspace
#
#   5. Full sandbox simulation (matches Stage 3 constraints exactly):
#      docker run --rm \
#        --network none \
#        --memory="16g" \
#        -v "$(pwd):/workspace" \
#        -v "/path/to/candidates.jsonl:/workspace/candidates.jsonl:ro" \
#        redrob-validator \
#        --csv /workspace/submission.csv \
#        --candidates /workspace/candidates.jsonl \
#        --repo-root /workspace
#
#   6. Run ranking code THEN validate (end-to-end sandbox test):
#      docker run --rm \
#        --network none \
#        --memory="16g" \
#        -v "$(pwd):/workspace" \
#        -v "/path/to/candidates.jsonl:/workspace/candidates.jsonl:ro" \
#        redrob-validator \
#        --run-rank \
#        --rank-cmd "python /workspace/rank.py --candidates /workspace/candidates.jsonl --out /workspace/submission.csv" \
#        --csv /workspace/submission.csv \
#        --candidates /workspace/candidates.jsonl \
#        --repo-root /workspace
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

FROM python:3.11-slim

LABEL maintainer="redrob-hackathon-validator"
LABEL description="Submission validator for Redrob Hackathon v4 — checks all spec requirements"

# Set environment
ENV PYTHONUNBUFFERED=1 \
    PYTHONDONTWRITEBYTECODE=1 \
    PIP_NO_CACHE_DIR=1

WORKDIR /app

# The validator only needs Python stdlib — no pip install needed
# Copy validation scripts
COPY validate_submission.py /app/validate_submission.py
COPY sandbox_runner.py /app/sandbox_runner.py

# Make scripts executable
RUN chmod +x /app/validate_submission.py /app/sandbox_runner.py

# Create workspace mount point
RUN mkdir -p /workspace

# Default entrypoint: the sandbox runner
ENTRYPOINT ["python", "/app/sandbox_runner.py"]

# Default args: validate submission.csv in workspace
CMD ["--csv", "/workspace/submission.csv", "--candidates", "/workspace/candidates.jsonl", "--repo-root", "/workspace"]
